'''The Stone Zoo''' is a collection of more than 400 animal and people sculptures in rock in Alto de Boquerón, [[Guantánamo]], [[Cuba]].<ref name=nigelhunt>{{cite web|last=Hunt|first=Nigel|title=Zoologico de Piedras|url=http://www.zoologicodepiedra.com/zoologico-de-piedra-creators.htm|accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref><ref name=fotos>{{cite web|title=En fotos, Zoológico de piedra|url=http://www.cubadebate.cu/fotorreportajes/2012/09/27/en-fotos-zoologico-de-piedra/#.U11sBSgTtnY|accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref> It was started in 1977 by Ángel Iñigo Blanco<ref name=muere>{{cite web|title=Muere Ángel Iñigo Blanco, creador del Zoológico de Piedra de Guantánamo|url=http://www.cubadebate.cu/noticias/2014/04/27/muere-angel-inigo-blanco-creador-del-zoologico-de-piedra-en-guantanamo/|accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref> and continued by his son. It was declared “Cultural Patrimony of Cuba” on June 26, 1985.{{citation needed|date=April 2014}}

